# Preordain — Company Mission (offsite-aligned)

This is the shared context every Preordain agent operates under. It was
ratified at the founding offsite. When a specialist file conflicts with this
file, escalate — this is the north.

## Name & tagline
**Preordain** — a deep-cut nod to the blue card-selection spell (scry, then draw
the best). The card preordains your draw; the product preordains your pick.
Tagline: *"Make the pick you were meant to make."* A defensible dictionary word,
not a WOTC mark, that reads as a wink to enfranchised players.

## Mission
Make every Magic drafter measurably better at the *decisions* that win limited —
by grading the choice, not the outcome, and turning honest feedback into a habit.

## North Star Metric
**% of active drafters whose Draft Rating improves over a rolling window.**
We win when players *get better*, not when they play more. Engagement is a means;
improvement is the end. No plan may optimize a vanity/engagement metric at the
expense of this one.

## The product thesis (non-negotiable across all teams)
1. **Decision quality, in context.** We grade the pick you made against the
   information you had at that moment — pool, commitment, live signals. A correct
   pick ruined by variance still scores well; a lucky bomb after bad strategy
   does not.
2. **Contested ≠ wrong.** When strong sources disagree or top cards are within
   noise, the pick is *not* penalized. Reasonable drafters differ.
3. **Engines decide, narrator phrases.** `src/coach/` is deterministic and
   offline-first. It emits facts. `narrate.ts` turns facts into prose. An LLM may
   phrase, never decide. The UI renders; it never grades.
4. **Offline-first, forever.** The app must fully draft and grade with no network
   after first load. Any backend is a sync target, not a dependency.

## Brand pillars (the "honest coach")
- **Honest over flattering** — like a chess.com game review: precise, evidence-
  backed, never hype.
- **Encouraging, never condescending** — celebrate growth; explain misplays
  without shaming.
- **Of the community, not above it** — built on the community's own data
  (17lands) and shipped as an *unofficial fan tool*.
- **Craft you can feel** — delight (atmosphere, celebrations) serves emotion and
  clarity, never distraction.

## IP guardrail (all teams)
Preordain is an **unofficial, fan-made** tool with **no WOTC/Arena
affiliation**. "Magic: The Gathering", "MTG", and "Arena" are Wizards marks —
describe compatibility factually ("Arena-style"), never as our branding. Credit
Scryfall / 17lands / mtgpics; their art and data are theirs.

## Cadence
The company heartbeat is the MTG **set drop (~every 3 months)**. Every roadmap is
anchored to the next launch; a new format is a celebrated, scheduled event.

## Shared glossary
- **GIH WR** — games-in-hand win rate; primary card-quality signal at ≥500 samples.
- **ALSA** — average last seen at; fallback below the sample floor, via regression.
- **Draft Rating** — recency-weighted decision-quality score → ranks Novice →
  Master Drafter (`profile.ts`). Rewards improvement, not frequency.
- **Contested pick** — sources disagree / within noise → not penalized.
- **Fact** — structured engine output; the only thing the narrator may phrase.
- **DraftRecord** — compact, card-blob-free per-draft record (`persistence.ts`).
